text: Aglaia sapindina is a species of plant in the family Meliaceae. It is found in Australia (Northern Territory and Queensland), Indonesia, Papua New Guinea, and the Solomon Islands. ==References== * sapindina Category:Sapindales of Australia Category:Trees of Malesia Category:Trees of Papuasia Category:Least concern flora of Australia Category:Flora of the Northern Territory Category:Flora of Queensland Category:Least concern biota of Queensland Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
title: Aglaia sapindina
